children.name: Text
children.value: Archie always makes the most fuss over the smallest things…

children.name: Text
children.value: Every time I ask Archie, I fear his insides combust.

children.name: Text
children.value: The best thing is, dear old Archie never need know.

children.name: Text
children.value: When a Queen asks you to do something…

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm issuing you a royal decree.

children.name: Text
children.value: I am the Queen after all.

children.name: Text
children.value: Yes, I jolly well think you will accept.

children.name: Text
children.value: Bon Voyage, as it is the fashion to say.

children.name: Text
children.value: Well done, you have my tender affections!

children.name: Text
children.value: I think we've both earned tea and a slice of sponge cake.

children.name: Text
children.value: What a daring young one you are!

children.name: Text
children.value: What gallantry! Though not quite worth a medal.

children.name: Text
children.value: As reliable as my guards with the funny hats.

children.name: Text
children.value: I was an obstinate child, and as such can empathise.

children.name: Text
children.value: And there was I believing I'd found a loyal dachsund.

children.name: Text
children.value: Need I tell you that you desert your nation!

children.name: Text
children.value: Like my coronation, a farce from beginning to end.

children.name: Text
children.value: My father would have had your head!

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't be afraid to hurry, we are happy to wait!

children.name: Text
children.value: Queens usually like things done quickly.

children.name: Text
children.value: At least bring me some tea if nothing else!

children.name: Text
children.value: You have served your Queen well, will you serve her again?

children.name: Text
children.value: It is a trying time for the Empire, and we need you yet...

children.name: Text
children.value: Your support is a comfort we would much like to continue.

children.name: Text
children.value: Who could possibly be more important than your Queen?

children.name: Text
children.value: I have not left the Palace in haste to be denied!

children.name: Text
children.value: Have you succeeded in your mission?

children.name: Text
children.value: I am told you may have something for me?

children.name: Text
children.value: I'll call upon you, subject, if I need you.

children.name: Text
children.value: There's nothing to keep you occupied here but my puppies.

children.name: Text
children.value: Dear Archie has everything under control.

children.name: Text
children.value: Oh do stop, Archie. Is this tiny fleet all I have to sink to get my island back?

children.name: Text
children.value: Who are you, to speak up without permission?

children.name: Text
children.value: So Edvard is the traitor! I certainly never authorised that silly-billy to act on my behalf. I declare the contract null and void.

children.name: Text
children.value: Then I suppose we'll not be sinking any ships today. Not even as a deterrent?

children.name: Text
children.value: Well in that case I hereby declare Prosperity returned to the Goode children— to compensate the dead father, thereby ensuring Miss Sarmento and co. are safe from this Pyrphorian nuisance.

children.name: Text
children.value: What is that tinseled marionette talking about, Archie? We are safe here, aren't we?

children.name: Text
children.value: Look at all those subjects! How enthusiastic they seem! Do you think they celebrate me, their royal highness?

children.name: Text
children.value: And you are absolutely sure this Samuel Goode was innocent?

children.name: Text
children.value: Let's heal it then, and be off.

children.name: Text
children.value: My sincerest condolences, children of Samuel. For the loss of the father you loved, and for the tragedy caused by the unfortunate actions of your uncle.

children.name: Text
children.value: For your unquestionable loyalty and bravery you shall be knighted, and bequeathed the island of Bright Sands from now and forevermore!

children.name: Text
children.value: Hahaha... Forgive me, I always laugh at funerals!

children.name: Text
children.value: But another tiresome prophet of doom, Archie. How dreary!

children.name: Text
children.value: These rebels, whoever they are, will pay the penalty for challenging my sovereignty!

children.name: Text
children.value: The time has come to take that territory back by force.

children.name: Text
children.value: Funny ending a war over a bit of paper!

children.name: Text
children.value: I must admit, I am too fond of my sailors.

children.name: Text
children.value: I understand this means the end of a rebellion on the island, very good.

children.name: Text
children.value: So is it Isabel who is nice, or the Pyrphorians?

children.name: Text
children.value: As long as we have Prosperity back, that business with your father can be forgotten.

children.name: Text
children.value: So Edvard was the nasty one, and Samuel was the one with dandruff?

children.name: Text
children.value: Fancy forging a signature. People can be terrible can't they?

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm surprised that Isabel gave it back without a fight.

children.name: Text
children.value: Once built, your Court of Justice shall inaugurate a new era of peace and prosperity for Empire.

children.name: Text
children.value: This trial should be a celebration! A toast to all things civilised.

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't normally attend trials so this one must be important.

children.name: Text
children.value: You now own the highest court in the land!

children.name: Text
children.value: Is the Court of Justice finished yet? Not quite?

children.name: Text
children.value: I can't wait to play judge and give the gavel a sharp tap!

children.name: Text
children.value: Did Archie tell you I planned to visit? I hope there's a convenient mooring for my flagship. I don't like long walks.

children.name: Text
children.value: Treat me as you would any other guest.

children.name: Text
children.value: Just so you know, I am not fond of garlic or profiteroles.

children.name: Text
children.value: One approves! And it is nice to get out and about.

children.name: Text
children.value: It all sounds very cheery so far. Make it cheerier.

children.name: Text
children.value: Mind you, I do like it when things are special. You can do special?

children.name: Text
children.value: May I express my gratitude for your sterling work preserving peace on the continent?

children.name: Text
children.value: So this is the funny little island that's hosting the trial! Jolly good.

children.name: Text
children.value: Now I'm here, I am of course impatient for the trial to begin.

children.name: Text
children.value: A modern Queen must show she is able to dispense mercy. The man must be given fair hearing.

children.name: Text
children.value: Now we are finally all present, let this long overdue trial commence!

children.name: Text
children.value: This is all rather unusual. We are safe here?

children.name: Text
children.value: This is unexpected. You are taking care of those beastly malefactors?

children.name: Text
children.value: A few angry hoodlums can't overthrow an Empire, can they?

children.name: Text
children.value: I thought they must be after fame or riches, but they want to kill me.

children.name: Text
children.value: I wonder what has become of the royal fleet…

children.name: Text
children.value: Tell me they are not attacking this island? The one we are on?

children.name: Text
children.value: I surrender myself wholly to your security arrangements.

children.name: Text
children.value: I suppose then, my safety is in your hands.

children.name: Text
children.value: When we get out of this I promise you a whole duchy. Although, no, I can't actually promise that.

children.name: Text
children.value: We are so happy to be finally allowed to leave this island. And for your heroism of course.

children.name: Text
children.value: Under different circumstances, you might have called it a pleasant visit!

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm sure we can make Isabel's tiny little chunk a protectorate of some sort.

children.name: Text
children.value: It makes one feel frisky and alive!

children.name: Text
children.value: How wonderful to have it our own way!

children.name: Text
children.value: It has all gone off very satisfactorily!

children.name: Text
children.value: All is much as it should be.

children.name: Text
children.value: Be strong in business, and become a pillar of our nation.

children.name: Text
children.value: You continue to be of the greatest use to us.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your successes must be a source of pride.

children.name: Text
children.value: You slide easily about the board like the rook!

children.name: Text
children.value: You are a very able servant of the realm.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Queen regrets this distressing affair.

children.name: Text
children.value: Another Queen may have turned to execution by now.

children.name: Text
children.value: It is gravely injurious to our nation.

children.name: Text
children.value: One wants prompt action against such outrage.

children.name: Text
children.value: It is a time of discord for those of my station.

children.name: Text
children.value: One of the many threats to my position.

children.name: Text
children.value: The Queen finds your conduct inexcusable!

children.name: Text
children.value: My father would have had you executed!
